{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "25", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "20", "M": "55", "S": "23"}}, "news": [{"title": "Eldeco Housing's net profit rises 12.93% to \u20b924.28 crore in FY26", "para": "Eldeco Housing & Industries reported a 12.93% rise in net consolidated profit for FY26, reaching \u20b924.28 crore. Total income also saw a significant increase of 22.29% to \u20b9175.71 crore. The company's board recommended a 450% final dividend, and it secured land parcels valued at \u20b92,000 crore GDV.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/eldeco-housing-achieves-1293-profit-growth-to-2428-crore-in-fy26/131312107?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-40284/131312107.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Awfis Space Solutions' net profit up 4.39% to \u20b970.85 crore in FY26", "para": "Awfis Space Solutions reported a 4.39% rise in net profit for FY26, reaching \u20b970.85 crore, with total income surging 25.81% to \u20b91,586.12 crore. The company expanded significantly, adding 41 new centres and 30,000 seats. Fourth-quarter profits saw a remarkable 106.95% jump. This growth highlights Awfis's strong performance and expansion strategy.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/awfis-space-solutions-reports-439-growth-in-net-profit-to-7085-crore-for-fy26/131311966?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-22398/131311966.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "HeidelbergCement India's profit falls over 10% to \u20b945.21 crore in Q4 FY26", "para": "HeidelbergCement India reported a 10.38% year-on-year decline in net profit to Rs 45.21 crore for the March quarter of FY26, primarily due to lower sales realization. Despite a 5.5% increase in revenue driven by higher sales volume, a 2% decrease in prices impacted profitability. The company recommended a 70% dividend for FY26.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/cement/heidelbergcement-india-reports-1038-profit-decline-to-4521-crore-in-q4-fy26/131312138?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-39932/131312138.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "cement"}, {"title": "Surya Roshni's net profit dips 17.54% to \u20b9285.81 crore in FY26", "para": "Surya Roshni reported a 17.54% decline in net consolidated profit for FY26, reaching \u20b9285.81 crore, despite a 1.73% increase in total income to \u20b97,594.39 crore. The company's managing director highlighted strong sales in March 2026 and a 7% revenue growth in lighting and consumer durables for FY26.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/lighting/consumer-lighting/surya-roshni-reports-1754-drop-in-fy26-profit-despite-revenue-growth/131307514?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-51640/131307514.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "lighting"}, {"title": "Shriram Properties' net profit up 30.41% to \u20b9100.81 crore in FY26", "para": "Shriram Properties witnessed a robust 30.41% surge in net profit for FY26, reaching \u20b9100.81 crore. Total income also climbed significantly by 39.40% to \u20b91,356.93 crore. The company reported strong sales bookings of \u20b92,354 crore and handed over 3,465 homes, while adding substantial new project pipelines.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/shriram-properties-reports-3041-surge-in-net-profit-to-10081-crore-for-fy26/131306672?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-77062/131306672.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Ajmera Realty's net profit up 18.93% to \u20b9149.79 crore in FY26", "para": "Ajmera Realty & Infra India reported a robust 18.93% rise in net profit for FY26, reaching \u20b9149.79 crore. Total income surged by 45.80% to \u20b91,098 crore. The company highlighted a significant five-year growth trajectory and ambitious targets for FY27, driven by new projects and its Wadala land bank.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/ajmera-realty-reports-3319-profit-surge-in-fy26-eyes-ambitious-fy27-target/131306413?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-21568/131306413.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "NBCC India's net profit rises 33.19% to \u20b9742.44 crore in FY26", "para": "NBCC (India) has announced a significant 33.19% surge in its net consolidated profit for FY26, reaching \u20b9742.44 crore. This growth was accompanied by a 7.52% increase in total income to \u20b913,195.88 crore. The company's board also recommended a final dividend of \u20b90.46 per share for FY26.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/nbcc-india-reports-3319-increase-in-net-profit-to-74244-crore-for-fy26/131305702?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-49482/131305702.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Kalpataru signs cluster redevelopment project in Kandivali East, Mumbai", "para": "Kalpataru has secured a significant cluster redevelopment project in Mumbai's Ashok Nagar, encompassing five societies across 2.8 acres. This venture boasts a substantial free sale potential of 0.37 million sq ft carpet area, with an estimated gross development value reaching \u20b91,250 crore. The company also reported robust financial performance in Q4 FY26, with pre-sales and collections showing impressive year-on-year growth.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/kalpataru-launches-major-redevelopment-project-in-kandivali-east-mumbai/131305351?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-89710/131305351.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Puravankara acquires 14.57-acre land parcel in Mandur, Bengaluru", "para": "Puravankara has acquired a 14.57-acre land parcel in Bengaluru's Mandur, Budigere, with a potential gross development value of \u20b92,300 crore. This acquisition, comprising both purchased land and a joint development agreement, will yield approximately 1.8 million sq ft of saleable area. The company's Bengaluru developable landbank now stands at 25.61 million sq ft.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/puravankara-acquires-1457-acres-in-bengaluru-a-boon-for-real-estate-development/131304740?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-235538/131304740.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "No decision to dismantle LIFE Mission housing scheme: Kerala's LSG minister", "para": "Kerala's Local Self Government Minister K M Shaji has clarified that the UDF government has no plans to disband the LIFE Mission housing scheme. He stated that restoring powers to grama sabhas does not equate to scrapping the project, emphasizing that the new government aims to correct shortcomings rather than dismantle existing initiatives.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/local-self-government-minister-clarifies-no-plans-to-dismantle-life-mission-housing-project/131301044?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-13822/131301044.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Bihar government seeks \u20b91,600 crore from centre for rural housing", "para": "In a significant move to bolster rural development, Bihar has formally requested the Centre to disburse Rs 1,600 crore under the 'Mother Sanction' for the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana\u2013Gramin. With the state's Single Nodal Account running low, timely support for beneficiaries is at risk.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/bihar-government-requests-1600-crore-funds-for-rural-housing-initiative/131300972?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-273840/131300972.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Buildings across city on Kolkata civic body's bulldozer list", "para": "Kolkata's civic body has issued 48-hour demolition notices to several 'unauthorised' buildings in Tiljala and Beleghata, leaving residents in distress. Many bought flats believing them to be legal, only to face displacement. Developers have vanished, leaving residents scrambling for answers and fearing for their families as authorities target 'red zones' with widespread illegal constructions.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/kolkatas-civic-body-targets-thousands-of-illegal-buildings-for-demolition/131300134?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-39482/131300134.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "SRA cracks down on 219 rehabilitation buildings in Mumbai without OC", "para": "The SRA has issued notices to over 200 buildings lacking Occupancy Certificates (OC) that have been handed over to slum dwellers. This crackdown follows the state government's amnesty scheme, aiming to regularize such structures and address issues like lack of maintenance funds and developers forcing early possession.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/sra-takes-action-against-219-mumbai-rehabilitation-buildings-without-occupancy-certificates/131300038?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-75193/131300038.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Supreme court's rule on OCs delays smart meter rollout in Karnataka", "para": "Karnataka's smart meter rollout faced significant delays due to confusion over mandatory occupancy certificates. While aimed at modernizing the power sector, the Supreme Court's order stalled new connections, impacting lakhs of applications. Recent government intervention has accelerated installations, with over three lakh smart meters now in place, though challenges persist for many awaiting connections.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/supreme-courts-ruling-halts-smart-meter-rollout-in-karnataka/131300021?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-42298/131300021.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Municipality identifies 49 unsafe buildings in Mapusa", "para": "Mapusa authorities have identified 49 structurally unsound buildings, including 42 private and 7 government structures, within municipal limits. A joint re-inspection drive, ordered by the North Goa district collector, flagged these buildings as dangerous ahead of the monsoon.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/mapusa-identifies-49-dangerous-buildings-ahead-of-monsoon-to-ensure-public-safety/131290220?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-75290/131290220.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Bengaluru civic bodies' revenue drops under khata conversion scheme", "para": "Bengaluru's civic bodies face a projected revenue loss of nearly Rs 1,015 crore due to a fee reduction for converting B-khata to A-khata properties. The \"Nanna Khata Nanna Hakku\" campaign offers a 100-day window to regularize properties at a reduced 2% guidance value.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/bengaluru-civic-bodies-revenue-drops-under-khata-conversion-scheme/131290185?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-32468/131290185.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Drain-top buildings to face higher tax in Sambhajinagar; crackdown on direct sewage discharge", "para": "Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar municipal corporation will raise property taxes for buildings constructed over major drains. This move aims to tackle monsoon flooding and improve desilting operations. The civic body also ordered strict action against direct sewage discharge into stormwater drains. Enforcement drives will ensure properties connect to sewage treatment plants.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/sambhajinagar-to-enforce-higher-property-tax-on-drain-top-buildings-amid-sewage-crackdown/131290128?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-680157/131290128.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Dehradun cancels registration of 103 homestays violating rules", "para": "Dehradun district administration has cancelled registrations of 103 homestays for violating safety norms and operational guidelines. Inspections revealed commercialization, illegal bars, and lack of basic facilities, leading to the crackdown following a surge in criminal activities. The administration is also removing these properties from the state tourism website.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/hospitality/dehradun-shuts-down-103-homestays-for-safety-violations-amid-rising-crime/131299946?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-26282/131299946.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "hospitality"}]}